üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. Cryptography is the science of:
A. Networking
B. Data compression
C. Secure communication
D. Data storage

2. Main goal of cryptography is to ensure:
A. Speed
B. Security
C. Redundancy
D. Availability only

3. A cipher is:
A. A key
B. An algorithm for encryption/decryption
C. A protocol
D. A password

4. Which type of encryption uses same key for encryption and decryption?
A. Asymmetric
B. Symmetric
C. Hybrid
D. Hashing

5. Which type of encryption uses two different keys?
A. Symmetric
B. Stream
C. Block
D. Asymmetric

6. Which is an example of symmetric algorithm?
A. RSA
B. AES
C. DSA
D. ECC

7. Which is an example of asymmetric algorithm?
A. DES
B. AES
C. RSA
D. Blowfish

8. A cryptographic key is:
A. Algorithm
B. Secret value
C. Plaintext
D. Ciphertext

9. Protocols are used to:
A. Encrypt data only
B. Define communication rules
C. Store data
D. Delete data

10. Which protocol secures web communication?
A. FTP
B. HTTP
C. HTTPS
D. SMTP

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. Which cryptographic goal ensures sender identity?
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity
C. Authentication
D. Availability

12. Which cipher encrypts data in fixed-size blocks?
A. Stream cipher
B. Block cipher
C. Hash function
D. Asymmetric cipher

13. AES is classified as:
A. Asymmetric block cipher
B. Symmetric block cipher
C. Symmetric stream cipher
D. Asymmetric stream cipher

14. Which is a disadvantage of symmetric encryption?
A. Slow processing
B. Key distribution problem
C. Large key size
D. No confidentiality

15. Which protocol was used before HTTPS for secure communication?
A. SSL
B. FTP
C. Telnet
D. SMTP

16. Asymmetric encryption is mainly used for:
A. Bulk data encryption
B. Key exchange
C. Compression
D. Hashing

17. Which key is shared publicly in asymmetric cryptography?
A. Secret key
B. Private key
C. Public key
D. Session key

18. Which protocol provides secure email?
A. HTTP
B. SSL
C. S/MIME
D. FTP

19. Key generation refers to:
A. Creating ciphertext
B. Creating encryption keys
C. Encrypting files
D. Sending keys

20. Ciphering a message means:
A. Deleting message
B. Compressing message
C. Encrypting message
D. Signing message

üî∫ ADVANCED LEVEL MCQs (10)
21. Which combination is correct?
A. RSA ‚Üí Symmetric
B. AES ‚Üí Asymmetric
C. RSA ‚Üí Asymmetric
D. DES ‚Üí Asymmetric

22. Why is asymmetric encryption slower?
A. Uses same key
B. Uses mathematical complexity
C. Uses small keys
D. Uses hashing

23. Which protocol uses both symmetric & asymmetric encryption?
A. FTP
B. HTTP
C. TLS/SSL
D. Telnet

24. In HTTPS, asymmetric encryption is used for:
A. Data transfer
B. Key exchange
C. Data compression
D. Hashing

25. Session keys are generally:
A. Asymmetric
B. Long-term keys
C. Symmetric
D. Public

26. Which protocol replaced SSL?
A. IPSec
B. TLS
C. SSH
D. SFTP

27. Which cryptographic primitive ensures integrity only?
A. Encryption
B. Hash function
C. Digital signature
D. Certificate

28. Cipher strength depends mainly on:
A. Algorithm name
B. Key length
C. File size
D. Network speed

29. Which attack targets weak cryptographic keys?
A. DoS
B. Brute force
C. Sniffing
D. Spoofing

30. CCEE MOST COMMON TRAP in cryptography is:
A. Symmetric vs Asymmetric confusion
B. Protocol purpose confusion
C. Key usage confusion
D. All of the above

‚úÖ ANSWER KEY
Basic:
1.C | 2.B | 3.B | 4.B | 5.D | 6.B | 7.C | 8.B | 9.B | 10.C

